Ranger Help for: reattune
=========================

SYNTAX:      reattune
             reattune primary <terrain>
             reattune secondary <terrain>
             reattune enemy <species>

USAGE:       Ranger lodge or Warden Thorn's meadow.

SUMMARY:
Warden Thorn can perform a reattunement ritual for Rangers who need to
change their primary terrain, secondary terrain, or enemy species after
their first choice.

The ritual cannot be performed while fighting or while you have an active
follower with you. It does not cost experience. After a successful
reattunement, your bond must settle for seven days before the ritual can be
performed again.

If you change your primary terrain and your current enemy species is not
valid for the new terrain, your enemy species will be cleared. Use 'setenemy'
to choose a new one.

Use 'reattune' with no arguments to see your current affinities, ritual
attunement state and cooldown.

